\section*{Methodology}
\label{sec:methodology}
Measurements of SPF and DMARC deployments across internet accessible second-level .gov domains were performed using \href{https://github.com/dhs-ncats/trustymail}{\underline{trustymail}}, our open source SPF/DMARC scanner, which checks the presence of:

\begin{enumerate}
  \item The domain in question;
  \item SPF, a TXT record that is queried out at the domain directly. (We do not check for SPF Resource Records, which \href{https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7208#section-3.1}{\underline{have been deprecated}}.); and
  \item DMARC, a TXT record that is queried at \texttt{\_dmarc.<domain>} and at \texttt{\_dmarc.<base\_domain>} as described in \href{https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7489}{\underline{RFC 7489}}, section 6.6.3.
\end{enumerate}
Results in this report were obtains from a scan performed on \usvardate\formatdate<<&title_date_tex>>.
Summary metrics from these scans were compiled and are reflected in the attached .CSV file.

